---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const u = (path: string) => `${base}${path}`;
---
<section class="deploy-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-label" style="text-align:center">Quick start</div>
    <h2 class="section-heading" style="text-align:center">Running in minutes.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub" style="text-align:center; margin: 0 auto 56px;">
      tidemarq is distributed as a Docker Compose stack. There's no package to install
      and no database to set up manually.
    </p>

    <div class="deploy-steps">
      <div class="deploy-step">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <h3>Configure</h3>
        <p>Download <code style="font-size:11px;color:var(--pale-teal);background:rgba(163,221,230,0.08);padding:2px 5px;border-radius:3px;">docker-compose.yml</code> and set your admin password via <code style="font-size:11px;color:var(--pale-teal);background:rgba(163,221,230,0.08);padding:2px 5px;border-radius:3px;">TIDEMARQ_ADMIN_PASSWORD</code></p>
      </div>
      <div class="deploy-step">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <h3>Start the stack</h3>
        <p>Run <code style="font-size:11px;color:var(--pale-teal);background:rgba(163,221,230,0.08);padding:2px 5px;border-radius:3px;">docker compose up</code> — the image is pulled automatically, TLS and admin credentials are generated on first start</p>
      </div>
      <div class="deploy-step">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <h3>Open the UI</h3>
        <p>Browse to <code style="font-size:11px;color:var(--pale-teal);background:rgba(163,221,230,0.08);padding:2px 5px;border-radius:3px;">https://localhost:8717</code> and log in with the credentials shown in the startup log</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-block" style="text-align:left">
      <div class="code-block-label">docker-compose.yml (excerpt)</div>
      <pre><span class="code-key">services:</span>
  <span class="code-key">tidemarq:</span>
    <span class="code-key">image:</span> <span class="code-val">ghcr.io/puckrin/tidemarq:latest</span>
    <span class="code-key">ports:</span>
      <span class="code-val">- "8716:8716"</span>   <span class="code-comment"># HTTP → redirects to HTTPS</span>
      <span class="code-val">- "8717:8717"</span>   <span class="code-comment"># HTTPS — main UI and API</span>
    <span class="code-key">volumes:</span>
      <span class="code-val">- ./data:/data</span>  <span class="code-comment"># persistent state</span></pre>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align:center; margin-top: 36px;">
      <a href={u('/docs/installation')} class="btn btn-primary">Read the full install guide</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
